<p></p>.<p><a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/dizziness_dizzy/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Dizziness</a> is a feeling of being lightheaded or woozy. Disturbances of 
the brain, gastrointestinal system, vision, and the <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/balance_disorders_pictures_slideshow/article.htm" rel="slide" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">vestibular system</a> of the inner 
ear are known causes of dizziness. People often refer to dizziness as <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/vertigo_overview/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">vertigo</a>, 
unsteadiness, or <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/dizziness_dizzy/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">lightheadedness</a>.</p>.<p class="credits">REFERENCE:<br><br>Kasper, D.L., et al., eds. <i>Harrison's Principles of Internal Medicine, 19th Ed</i>. United States: McGraw-Hill Education, 2015.</p>